The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, will on Wednesday, 12th January, 2022, carry out the screening of aspirants for the Osun State governorship election primary. Tuesday, 11th January, 2022, had earlier been fixed for the screening of the aspirants by the party. A statement issued by Umar M. Nature, the National Organising Secretary of the Party, explained that the screening exercise had been set to begin 10 a.m. at the PDP National Secretariat, Abuja. According to him, the party regrets any inconveniences the change in date may have caused. The statement explained, “All aspirants, leaders, critical stakeholders and members of our party in Osun State should take note and by this, guided accordingly.”